{{about|skater Jeanne Chevalier|writer Jean Chevalier|Jean Chevalier}} {{Infobox figure skater |name= Jeanne Chevalier |image= |caption= |country= [[Canada]] |birth_date= |death_date= |partner= [[Norman M. Scott]] |formercoach= |formerchoreographer= |skating club= Winter Club of Montreal |retired= }}
'''Jeanne Chevalier''' was a [[Canadian]] [[figure skater]] who competed in both [[single skating]] and [[pair skating]]. Her pairs partner was [[Norman M. Scott]]. As a single skater, she is the 1920 and 1921 [[Canadian Figure Skating Championships|Canadian champion]]. She and Scott won the 1914 Canadian pairs title. Chevalier was part of the four teams that won the Canadian fours championships in 1910, 1920 and 1921.
She also competed in the United States and won the first [[United States Figure Skating Championships]] in pairs.
